title: Netanyahu Extends Lead in Israel Election, Projections Say
description: Benjamin Netanyahu’s near-certain victory in this week’s election in Israel won’t be confirmed until Thursday, but his far right allies are already savoring their rise to power.
dc:creator: Patrick Kingsley
media:credit: Amit Elkayam for The New York Times
media:description: Benjamin Netanyahu, right, in Jerusalem on Tuesday. With about two-thirds of the vote counted, Israel’s three main broadcasters were projecting that Mr. Netanyahu’s party, Likud, would finish first.
